<section class="caregiver-economics-section">
  <div class="container caregiver-economics-inner">
    <div>
      <p class="overline">Caregiver economics</p>
      <h2>Premium follows the use, not the store account.</h2>
      <p>Premium subscriptions are managed by the App Store or Google Play account that buys them. Caregivers on separate store accounts, such as nannies, grandparents, postpartum doulas, or daycare staff, usually need their own Premium subscription unless the household buys the device once.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="economics-table-wrap">
      <table class="economics-table">
        <caption>Caregiver Premium cost and device payback comparison</caption>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th scope="col">Household with non-family caregivers</th>
            <th scope="col">Annual Premium without device</th>
            <th scope="col">Device payback</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><th scope="row">Two parents + nanny</th><td>$79.98</td><td>About 13 months</td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">Two parents + nanny + 1 grandparent</th><td>$119.97</td><td>About 9 months</td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">Two parents + nanny + 2 grandparents</th><td>$159.96</td><td>About 7 months</td></tr>
          <tr><th scope="row">Two parents + daycare staff logging on their own devices</th><td>$79.98+</td><td>About 13 months+</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p class="economics-note">Method: $89.99 device cost divided by the annual Premium cost the household would otherwise pay across separate store accounts.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

